 over-the-counter medicines in France.<a title="Vickers AJ, Smith C. Homoeopathic Oscillococcinum for preventing and treating influenza and influenza-like syndromes. Cochrane Database Syst Rev, 2006; 3: CD001957." href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD001957.pub3/abstract;jsessionid=3E05CC7D98135B0B4BD1AABDF09B59B4.f01t04" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><sup>5</sup></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span class="accent">UK</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>10% of people in the UK use homeopathy – an estimated 6 million people.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Britain, the market for homeopathy is growing at around 20% per year.  In 2007, it was estimated to be worth £38m, and is projected to reach £46m in 2012.</li>\r\n 	<li>In the NHS approx. 40,000 homeopathic prescriptions are provided to patients per year by doctors working within the homeopathic service. There were originally 5 homeopathic hospitals (Glasgow, Liverpool, London, Bristol and Tunbridge Wells). Tunbridge Wells closed in 2007 and earlier this year the Royal London Homeopathic Hospital changed its name to the Royal London Hospital for Integrated Medicine.</li>\r\n 	<li>There are ~ 400 doctors in the UK that use homeopathy, regulated by the Faculty of Homeopathy and promoted by the British Homeopathic Association.</li>\r\n 	<li>There and ~1,500 professional homeopaths (non-medically qualified homeopaths) in the UK, regulated by the Society of Homeopaths (65%), Alliance of Registered Homeopaths and Homeopathic Medical Association. They largely operate in private practice outside the NHS.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://www.hri-research.org/resources/homeopathy-the-debate/hri-facts/homeopathy-within-the-national-health-service-uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">See NHS spending on homeopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span class="accent">US</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>According to the National Institutes of Health, over 6 million people in the United States use homeopathy, mainly for self-care of specific health conditions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What homeopathy costs?</h2>\r\nYour first consultation with a private homeopath will usually cost between INR 500 to INR 10,000. Further appointments usually cost less – about INR 500 to INR 5000 depending on the location of the place and experience of homeopath. It will also depend on the skill level of his staff or assistants who usually take the first case and prepare it for the main consultant.\r\n\r\nYour remedy will usually be included in the consultation price, but do check this first. Homeopathic tablets or other products usually cost around INR 100 to INR500 if you need to buy them separately in India.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2341" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2341" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/DR.-KHEDEKAR.-KHEDEKAR-300x167.png" alt="" width="300" height="167" /> Imperial clinics Mumbai[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b><a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Dr. Shreepad A. Khedekar, BHMS, MD</a> (homeopathy), a specialist for over 17 years, he has used homeopathy in his Switzerland, Belgrade and Mumbai practice for the last 17 years. He lectures in homeopathy at Switzerland, Croatia and at the Serbian Doctors Association (SLD) Teaching Centre in Belgrade and has a busy private practice in Dadar, Mumbai and at Shushrusha Citizens co-operative hospital, Mumbai and is the only Homeopath in their 60 year history.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Shreepad</a> <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Khedekar</a>  is the Clinical Director, Imperial clinics Mumbai and Imperial clinics Belgrade, Consultant at Shushrusha Citizens Co-op Hospital Mumbai and Physician to several international stars and celebrities.</b>\r\n\r\nPlease do take a look at his CV: <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'What does it take to be a homeopath in India?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-08-11 09:52:15', '2017-08-11 09:52:15', '', 70, 'http://eheilung.com/ehblog/?p=71', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '<strong>What''s the need for a Stress Calculator?</strong>\r\n\r\nRevolutions are not born of chance but of necessity. And it is imperative today that we have a healthcare system that is broader than just a quick fix solution that''s guided by profit.\r\n\r\nOn World Homeopathy day, we would like to introduce a revolution in healthcare. A system that enables you to diagnose and treat yourself using Homeopathic tools that through its simplicity, efficiency and affordability will improve millions of lives around the world in the most natural way.\r\n\r\nFor<span class="text_exposed_show"> the first phase of our launch, download our Stress Calculator app from Google Play <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.eheilung.stress" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details…</a> and It will accurately determine your stress levels (the root cause of most diseases) and recommend how to deal with it in a holistic way. </span>\r\n<div class="text_exposed_show">\r\n\r\nThe next phase will enable you to diagnose and manage your ailments like never before.\r\n\r\nEveryone deserves good health and happiness!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>Why check stress levels?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe situations and pressures that cause stress are known as stressors. We usually think of stressors as being negative, such as an exhausting work schedule or a difficult relationship. However, anything that puts high demands on you can be stressful. This includes positive events such as getting married, buying a house, going to college, or receiving a promotion.\r\nOf course, not all stress is caused by external factors. Stress can also be internal or self-generated, when you worry excessively about something that may or may not happen, or have irrational, pessimistic thoughts about life.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is stress?</strong>\r\n\r\nStress is your body’s way of responding to any kind of demand or threat. When you feel threatened, your nervous system responds by releasing a flood of stress hormones, including adrenaline and cortisol, which rouse the body for emergency action. Your heart pounds faster, muscles tighten, blood pressure rises, breath quickens, and your senses become sharper. These physical changes increase your strength and stamina, speed your reaction time, and enhance your focus. This is known as the “fight or flight” or mobilization stress response and is your body’s way of protecting you.\r\nWhen stress is within your comfort zone, it can help you to stay focused, energetic, and alert. In emergency situations, stress can save your life—giving you extra strength to defend yourself, for example, or spurring you to slam on the brakes to avoid an accident. Stress can also help you rise to meet challenges. Stress is what keeps you on your toes during a presentation at work, sharpens your concentration when you’re attempting the game-winning free throw, or drives you to study for an exam when you''d rather be watching TV. But beyond your comfort zone, stress stops being helpful and can start causing major damage to your mind and body leading to disease.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are the effects of chronic stress?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe body’s nervous system often does a poor job of distinguishing between daily stressors and life-threatening events. If you’re stressed over an argument with a friend, a traffic jam on your commute, or a mountain of bills, for example, your body can still react as if you’re facing a life-or-death situation.\r\nWhen you repeatedly experience the mobilization or fight-or-flight stress response in your daily life, it can lead to serious health problems. Chronic stress disrupts nearly every system in your body. It can shut down your immune system, upset your digestive and reproductive systems, raise blood pressure, increase the risk of heart attack and stroke, speed up the aging process and leave you vulnerable to many mental and physical health problems.\r\n\r\n<strong>Try our Stress Calculator now by installing it on your android phone.</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2507" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2507" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Image-4-2-300x223.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="223" /> US consul General, His Excellency Peter Haas giving the award of OutStanding Achiever to Dr. Shreepad Khedekar[/caption]\r\n<h2>What homeopathy costs?</h2>\r\nYour first consultation with a private homeopath will usually cost between INR 500 to INR 10,000. Further appointments usually cost less – about INR 500 to INR 5000 depending on the location of the place and experience of homeopath. It will also depend on the skill level of his staff or assistants who usually take the first case and prepare it for the main consultant.\r\n\r\nYour remedy will usually be included in the consultation price, but do check this first. Homeopathic tablets or other products usually cost around INR 100 to INR500 if you need to buy them separately in India.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2341" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2341" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/DR.-KHEDEKAR.-KHEDEKAR-300x167.png" alt="" width="300" height="167" /> Imperial clinics Mumbai[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b><a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Dr. Shreepad A. Khedekar, BHMS, MD</a> (homeopathy), a specialist for over 17 years, he has used homeopathy in his Switzerland, Belgrade and Mumbai practice for the last 17 years. He lectures in homeopathy at Switzerland, Croatia and at the Serbian Doctors Association (SLD) Teaching Centre in Belgrade and has a busy private practice in Dadar, Mumbai and at Shushrusha Citizens co-operative hospital, Mumbai and is the only Homeopath in their 60 year history.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Shreepad</a> <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Khedekar</a>  is the Clinical Director, Imperial clinics Mumbai and Imperial clinics Belgrade, Consultant at Shushrusha Citizens Co-op Hospital Mumbai and Physician to several international stars and celebrities.</b>\r\n\r\nPlease do take a look at his CV: <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'How to calculate your Stress levels?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-calculate-your-stress-levels', '', '', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '', 0, 'http://eheilung.com/ehblog/?p=72', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '<strong>What''s the need for a Stress Calculator?</strong>\r\n\r\nRevolutions are not born of chance but of necessity. And it is imperative today that we have a healthcare system that is broader than just a quick fix solution that''s guided by profit.\r\n\r\nOn World Homeopathy day, we would like to introduce a revolution in healthcare. A system that enables you to diagnose and treat yourself using Homeopathic tools that through its simplicity, efficiency and affordability will improve millions of lives around the world in the most natural way.\r\n\r\nFor<span class="text_exposed_show"> the first phase of our launch, download our Stress Calculator app from Google Play <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.eheilung.stress" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details…</a> and It will accurately determine your stress levels (the root cause of most diseases) and recommend how to deal with it in a holistic way. </span>\r\n<div class="text_exposed_show">\r\n\r\nThe next phase will enable you to diagnose and manage your ailments like never before.\r\n\r\nEveryone deserves good health and happiness!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>Why check stress levels?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe situations and pressures that cause stress are known as stressors. We usually think of stressors as being negative, such as an exhausting work schedule or a difficult relationship. However, anything that puts high demands on you can be stressful. This includes positive events such as getting married, buying a house, going to college, or receiving a promotion.\r\nOf course, not all stress is caused by external factors. Stress can also be internal or self-generated, when you worry excessively about something that may or may not happen, or have irrational, pessimistic thoughts about life.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is stress?</strong>\r\n\r\nStress is your body’s way of responding to any kind of demand or threat. When you feel threatened, your nervous system responds by releasing a flood of stress hormones, including adrenaline and cortisol, which rouse the body for emergency action. Your heart pounds faster, muscles tighten, blood pressure rises, breath quickens, and your senses become sharper. These physical changes increase your strength and stamina, speed your reaction time, and enhance your focus. This is known as the “fight or flight” or mobilization stress response and is your body’s way of protecting you.\r\nWhen stress is within your comfort zone, it can help you to stay focused, energetic, and alert. In emergency situations, stress can save your life—giving you extra strength to defend yourself, for example, or spurring you to slam on the brakes to avoid an accident. Stress can also help you rise to meet challenges. Stress is what keeps you on your toes during a presentation at work, sharpens your concentration when you’re attempting the game-winning free throw, or drives you to study for an exam when you''d rather be watching TV. But beyond your comfort zone, stress stops being helpful and can start causing major damage to your mind and body leading to disease.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are the effects of chronic stress?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe body’s nervous system often does a poor job of distinguishing between daily stressors and life-threatening events. If you’re stressed over an argument with a friend, a traffic jam on your commute, or a mountain of bills, for example, your body can still react as if you’re facing a life-or-death situation.\r\nWhen you repeatedly experience the mobilization or fight-or-flight stress response in your daily life, it can lead to serious health problems. Chronic stress disrupts nearly every system in your body. It can shut down your immune system, upset your digestive and reproductive systems, raise blood pressure, increase the risk of heart attack and stroke, speed up the aging process and leave you vulnerable to many mental and physical health problems.\r\n\r\n<strong>Try our Stress Calculator now by installing it on your android phone.</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2507" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2507" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Image-4-2-300x223.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="223" /> US consul General, His Excellency Peter Haas giving the award of OutStanding Achiever to Dr. Shreepad Khedekar[/caption]\r\n<h2>What homeopathy costs?</h2>\r\nYour first consultation with a private homeopath will usually cost between INR 500 to INR 10,000. Further appointments usually cost less – about INR 500 to INR 5000 depending on the location of the place and experience of homeopath. It will also depend on the skill level of his staff or assistants who usually take the first case and prepare it for the main consultant.\r\n\r\nYour remedy will usually be included in the consultation price, but do check this first. Homeopathic tablets or other products usually cost around INR 100 to INR500 if you need to buy them separately in India.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2341" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2341" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/DR.-KHEDEKAR.-KHEDEKAR-300x167.png" alt="" width="300" height="167" /> Imperial clinics Mumbai[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b><a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Dr. Shreepad A. Khedekar, BHMS, MD</a> (homeopathy), a specialist for over 17 years, he has used homeopathy in his Switzerland, Belgrade and Mumbai practice for the last 17 years. He lectures in homeopathy at Switzerland, Croatia and at the Serbian Doctors Association (SLD) Teaching Centre in Belgrade and has a busy private practice in Dadar, Mumbai and at Shushrusha Citizens co-operative hospital, Mumbai and is the only Homeopath in their 60 year history.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Shreepad</a> <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Khedekar</a>  is the Clinical Director, Imperial clinics Mumbai and Imperial clinics Belgrade, Consultant at Shushrusha Citizens Co-op Hospital Mumbai and Physician to several international stars and celebrities.</b>\r\n\r\nPlease do take a look at his CV: <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'How to calculate your Stress levels?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '2017-08-11 09:53:25', '', 72, 'http://eheilung.com/ehblog/?p=73', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2017-08-11 09:54:19', '2017-08-11 09:54:19', '<h2 class="strakline">When it comes to autism, the focus of homeopathy is to treat the child as a whole and not just the symptoms says Dr Shreepad Khedekar MD (hom) for autism treatment in homeopathy and autism recovery in homeopathy.</h2>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mrpz7rQZuk8&t=4s\r\n<div class="edi-date fl eventtracker" data-event-sub-cat="Author" data-event-title="yes"><span class="edi-date fl"><a href="http://www.thehealthsite.com/author/sandhya-raghavan/">by Sandhya Raghavan  </a></span></div>\r\n<div class="fr art-del-sc">\r\n<div class="clear">\r\n\r\nImagine your child smothering you in hugs and kisses when you come back home after work. Truly priceless.  But did you know that many parents in the world are denied of this simple yet beautiful pleasure because their children fail to acknowledge their presence? It’s not because these children are antisocial, it’s because they have autism, a developmental disability that afflicts one in every thousand children, taking away their ability to communicate and forge relationships with others using language. Read: 5 shocking things that can increase the risk of autism in children.\r\n\r\nConvention treatment for autism leaves a lot to be desired since it only focuses on treating the symptoms of the disorder and not the child. The world is now slowly waking up to the powers of alternative medicines especially when it comes to treating disorders on the autistic spectrum. One such discipline that has seen brilliant results in not only treating but also reversing autism is homoeopathy.\r\n\r\nOn April 10, World Homeopathy Day, we spoke to renowned homoeopath Dr Shreepad Khedekar from Imperial Clinics about his take on autism and how homoeopathy works towards stimulating the child’s DNA to correct the disorder, helping him or her cure autism rather than learning how to function around it. Dr Khedekar is an authority in the field of paediatric developmental disorder management, and he has initiated a seven-year-old international study involving children with issues such as delayed development, autism, tuberous sclerosis, dyspraxia, borderline Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD) and cerebral palsy. Autism treatment in homeopathy, Autism recovery homeopathy how is that possible? How is ADHD homeopathic treatment done, will homeopathy for ADHD work?\r\n\r\n<strong>What is wrong with conventional treatment methods?</strong>\r\n\r\n“In autism, there is a complete breakdown in coordination between mental activities,” says Dr Khedekar. “In the conventional system of medicine, the treatment for autism is not the best; it, in fact, is very suppressive in nature. Remedies are given to suppress the hyperactivity of child can be suppressed, or they try to take care of the secondary effects of autism, like its complications. The answer to curing rather than just managing autism lies in the DNA of the child according to Dr Khedekar. “The repair has to be done at the level of the child’s DNA. Only then can you bring it out of autism. This is what I call the genetic repair process. Through homoeopathy, we stimulate the child’s own repair mechanism,” he adds. The focus of the treatment and management through homoeopathy is not to treat the isolated symptoms of the developmental disorder, but to treat the child as a whole and help in building up the personality traits of the child from the time of the treatment.\r\n\r\n<strong>What causes autism according to homoeopathy?</strong>\r\n\r\nDr Khedekar says that it is difficult to pinpoint exact causes of autism. But in his experience, he has come across certain factors that were common in most of the cases.\r\n\r\n•    Stress during pregnancy- Dr Khedekar says, “50% of the time, stress during pregnancy is a positive finding. Mother’s mental health during the time of pregnancy can impact the development of the child. “In most cases, the mother was going through stress during pregnancy such problems with the husband or the in-laws,” recounts Dr Khedekar.\r\n\r\n•    Mercurial compounds in vaccines – “Some newly introduced vaccines can be a trigger for autism mainly due to their mercurial compounds,” states Dr Khedekar. “Although there are no studies to support this, I have found this to be a trigger in my experience.”\r\n\r\n<strong>What are the signs of autism in children?</strong>\r\n\r\nDr Khedekar says that the initial symptoms of the disorder start showing at two years of age. Following are some of the most conspicuous symptoms of the disorder.\r\n\r\n•    Lack of eye contact in the child\r\n\r\n•    No separation anxiety is seen in the child on being taken away from its parents\r\n\r\n•    No emotional attachment towards parents or caregivers\r\n\r\n•    Prefers to stay alone and play solitary games\r\n\r\n•    Does not make friends\r\n\r\n•    Impaired verbal skills. Cannot make full sentences\r\n\r\n•    Repetitive activities like pinching oneself, banging head, rubbing genitals\r\n\r\n•    Attachment towards inanimate objects like toys\r\n\r\nAlthough the symptoms start showing only after two years, the actual damage happens when the child is in the womb. “When the mother is going through stress, the child, even in utero, uses its intelligence to fend off the effects of the adverse conditions in its mother’s womb,” he says. This is when the developmental disorder starts taking shape.\r\n\r\n<strong>How does homoeopathy treat autism?</strong>\r\n\r\n•    Good behaviour therapy – The child has to be left in the care of a therapist who can mould the child’s behaviour. This will bring out a positive change in the child who will be taught basic skills like looking, listening, reading, conversing and mimicking.\r\n\r\n•    A good diet – In Dr Khedekar’s experience with autistic children, he has found that most have some sensitivity to proteins such as casein (found commonly in milk) and gluten. “A diet free of these two can go a long way in helping the child fight autism,” he emphasises.\r\n\r\n•      A good homoeopathic remedy- Finally, formulating the right homoeopathic remedy is the last step in curing the child. For this, prescriptions should be made through observations. The child has to be understood as a whole and not just as a clutch of symptoms. So understanding the child’s mind and body is important in curing autism.\r\n\r\n<strong>How homoeopathy works</strong>\r\n\r\nTo formulate a similimum or a cure, a homoeopath has to observe the child acutely for its behaviour and preferences. “The doctor makes a note of the child’s behaviour, whether it is screaming, shouting, crawling or performing repetitive behaviours. He will also observe whether the child prefers warmer or cooler temperatures or sweet or sour foods,” the doctor states. This, according to Dr Khedekar, gives the homoeopath insights into the child’s genetic makeup, which will in turn help in formulating the right homoeopathic remedy. Once the remedy is administered, the genetic reversal is triggered and the child is cured.\r\n\r\n<strong>Way forward</strong>\r\n\r\nSceptics should know that autistic children treated with homoeopathy were monitored by Dr Khedekar in a seven-year-long study. Pre and post-treatment observations have found that 80 percent of these children are living physically and psychologically balanced lives! Even when convention medicine gropes in the dark looking for answers, homoeopathy has proved that a seemingly complex disorder like autism can be reversed with simple and holistic steps.\r\n\r\n<em>Dr Shreepad Khedekar has treated world famous <strong>Tennis Star Novak Djokovic </strong>for asthma. Has also cured many European football stars playing the European Premier League. Has his own practice in Europe and believes in research, has submitted hundreds of case studies to medical journals internationally. He is a physician, teacher, researcher, and author. He has written four books on Homeopathy. He operates through his clinics in Dadar and Belgrade and is also a consultant at Shushrusha Hospital, Mumbai.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>For more details: www.imperialclinics.com</em></strong>\r\n<h2>What homeopathy costs?</h2>\r\nYour first consultation with a private homeopath will usually cost between INR 500 to INR 10,000. Further appointments usually cost less – about INR 500 to INR 5000 depending on the location of the place and experience of homeopath. It will also depend on the skill level of his staff or assistants who usually take the first case and prepare it for the main consultant.\r\n\r\nYour remedy will usually be included in the consultation price, but do check this first. Homeopathic tablets or other products usually cost around INR 100 to INR500 if you need to buy them separately in India.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_2341" align="alignnone" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-2341" src="http://imperialclinics.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/DR.-KHEDEKAR.-KHEDEKAR-300x167.png" alt="" width="300" height="167" /> Imperial clinics Mumbai[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b><a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Dr. Shreepad A. Khedekar, BHMS, MD</a> (homeopathy), a specialist for over 17 years, he has used homeopathy in his Switzerland, Belgrade and Mumbai practice for the last 17 years. He lectures in homeopathy at Switzerland, Croatia and at the Serbian Doctors Association (SLD) Teaching Centre in Belgrade and has a busy private practice in Dadar, Mumbai and at Shushrusha Citizens co-operative hospital, Mumbai and is the only Homeopath in their 60 year history.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Shreepad</a> <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">Khedekar</a>  is the Clinical Director, Imperial clinics Mumbai and Imperial clinics Belgrade, Consultant at Shushrusha Citizens Co-op Hospital Mumbai and Physician to several international stars and celebrities.</b>\r\n\r\nPlease do take a look at his CV: <a href="http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum">http://imperialclinics.com/dr-shreepad-khedekar-imperial-clinics-autism-spectrum</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'World Homeopathy Awareness Week: Can homeopathy treat Autism and ADHD?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'world-homeopathy-awareness-week-can-homeopathy-treat-autism-and-adhd', '', '', '2017-08-11 09:55:19', '2017-08-11 09:55:19', '', 0, 'http://eheilung.com/ehblog/?p=74', 0, 'post', '', 0),
